Text.string: Aghhh!
Way ahead of you, Lil. Vault Hunter, come down to the cargo bay and let's chat.
Maliwan's never come down here before. If they think we're easy targets now that they've got bandit backup... oh, they're about to learn differently. Come on!
Hey. Listen, I know Lil's puttin' on a good face, but she's hurtin'. We're all gonna have to pick up the slack. I know you're up to it, sweet cheeks.
Come a long way for this Vault, haven't ya? If there is one here, maybe that's what Maliwan's REALLY after.
I'm not picking up any signals from Atlas. Maliwan must be jamming their comms.
Atlas Command, come in! We're being overrun! Send reinforcements!
Sounded like an Atlas distress call. They need help down there.
That distress call was coming from the city outskirts. We need to get you down to the surface, but we don't have access to the Promethean Fast-Travel network.
Command, do you copy? Send backup! Atlas Command! Damn it, we've got bandits coming out of thin bloody air!
Slag me, you've got some good timing! These bandits somehow got their hands on some wicked Maliwan guns. Oh, right—I'm Lorelei. Did Rhys send you?
Heya superfan!
You finally made it! We've been here for ages. Oh! Thank Lilith for the cool powers. This Firehawk thing RULES! Oh, have fun! Bye!
Come get it, you tossers!
I'll take you all on!
Piss off!
You messed with the wrong city!
Get on, you psychos!
Is that all?! Come at me!
Where are my bloody reinforcements?!
Get to cover, I'll hold them off!
Ngh! Bloody...
Ugh, bloody hell, I got bandit all over me...||—Hey, you! Over here!
I don't know a Rhys.
Who's Rhys?
Who or what is a “Rhys”?
Rhys? No clue, sorry.
Thank the Calypsos for that. I'm here to reach the Vault before they do.
That's the Calypsos' doing. They want the Vault, and I'm here to beat them to it.
This is the work of the Calypsos. I am hunting the Vault to keep its power out of their grasp.
That's those Calypso shiteheads. I'm trying to beat them to the Vault myself.

The Calypsos? Those yammering ECHOnet assholes with the cult? Well, I got no slagging clue about Vaults, but Rhys would know. Come on, I gotta tell him about our new bandit problem anyway. I'll introduce you.
Grab some wheels. We need to drive through the spillways, and there's always trouble.
My boss? CEO of Atlas? We're at war with Maliwan? Not from around here, are you? Heh, now all these maniacs show up all over the city screaming about some Vault.
Maliwan pushed most of the Atlas forces back to HQ, but I've got a small team working behind enemy lines. I have to make sure they haven't been overrun with all these bandits running around.

I'll be honest. Atlas forces are gutted. I've been using what resources I've got left to keep the civs safe and disrupt Maliwan supply lines. Can't remember the last time I slept in a bed. Ugh, I miss coffee.
I wasn't always a soldier, you know. Used to be a barista before this war broke out. Bloody good one, too. There's a big crater where my cafe used to be. Shame. Some things you can never get back.
This is our stop. On foot from here.
Oi, Skyman! Open up!
Uh. Password?
Password's “open the bloody door before I shove a coffee grinder up your ass”.
It's definitely her, guys! Welcome back, sir!
See these civilians? Maliwan doesn't care if they're caught in the crossfire. They're here to take over Atlas and sell Rhys' new weapons as their own. To them, this war is just a merger.
What? Bandits? How did they beat us here?
Come on. We're heading to Watershed Base. It's through here. Maliwan's bloody well entrenched, so get ready for a fight.
Bloody digistruct torpedoes! They're sending in reinforcements!
Bloody hell, that got a bit mucky. Thought we were sorted back there.||—Hey you, over here!
Pyrotechs! Look out!
Ugh, slag me! The bandits are working with Maliwan! Bloody fantastic.
Get wasted, you wankers! That was brilliant, Vault Hunter.
Rhys, relax, it's Lorelei. We've taken back Watershed Base, with a little help. I've got—hang about, WHAT is that thing on your face?
Oh this? This is my... siege mustache. The troops love it. Anyway, uh, who's your friend?
I'm a Vault Hunter. I'm on a mission for the Crimson Raiders.
I'm a Vault Hunter. And I'm here with the Crimson Raiders.
I am a Vault Hunter. And a Crimson Raider.
Guess I'm a Vault Hunter now.||And a Crimson Raider.||And a handsome bastard.||I'm a lot of things.
They're good, Rhys. Really good. And we need all the help we can get. Bandits are pouring into the city, and they're working WITH Maliwan. Looks like Katagawa's made a deal with the Calypsos.
Right. While you go meet Rhys' agent, I'm gonna get this base back online and start securing more of the city.||Oh—before you head off, I've got something for you.
Superfan! So, what do you think of our first corporate sponsors? I gotta say, so far, selling out rules!
We gave Maliwan an unlimited supply of screaming war-meat, a.k.a. our followers. And they gave us a bunch of crazy high-tech guns.
My people are inside. Let me do the talking.
And once they take the planet, they get Atlas, and we get the Vault. So, you're left playing with... whatever you got down there! Just keep doin' you! Ha!
Looks like Rhys' agent is in the mercantile plaza. Maliwan's got a weapons depot set up inside the mall and I'll bet bollocks to bullets that's what he's after.
Haywire service bots. / Their masters have long since fled. / Decommission them.
All bots demolished. / Lower that shield so we can / loot some sweet weapons.
We made them angry. / Prepare for counterattack. / Maliwan dickheads.
Here they come now. Fools. / They approach their certain deaths. / Let us oblige them.
So, what's our target?
What are we looking for?
What are we hunting for?
All right, what's our next thing?
New Maliwan tech. / My sword requires an upgrade. / Search through this depot.
A-ha. The upgrade. / Bring it to me, Vault Hunter. / It is quite vital.
Hey, it's Rhys' best friend Zer0, stealing my tech. What's wrong? Atlas not “cutting it” anymore? My offer still stands. It's not too late to come work for Maliwan.
What was that?!
That's Katagawa. / Head of Maliwan Mergers. / And Acquisitions.
And YOU must be the Vault Hunter Tyreen warned me about. You know what, I don't even have time for you. I'll let my superior forces do the talking.
You're small stuff, Vault Hunter. Not worth my time. Mess with my Gigamind, though, and that'll change. You keep playing under the feet of giants, you're gonna get stepped on.
Containment breach! GOING CRITICAL!
Yikes.

Wow. You really just popped the brains right out of my Gigamind. Not satisfied with running underfoot, huh? I get it. My father once said I was twelfth in line to run the company. So I made eleven quick little cuts to the family tree. Now, I'm next in line. Think about that, now you've put yourself in my way.
Welcome back, Vault Hunter! Wait, why do you smell like brains and fried circuitry? You know what, I don't want to know. Call Rhys and let him know you got the job done.
And then you'll help us get to the Vault. Right?
Oh, I got it. But I want your word you'll help us open the Vault.
I have it. But you must promise to help us get to the Vault.
Yeah, I got it. But I ain't givin' it unless you help us open the Vault.
I mean... I can just toss this brain in the trash if no one's gonna use it.
So you don't mind if I throw this brain in a drainage ditch?
Perhaps my beast would enjoy this brain as a snack.
Your loss! I'm gonna see how far I can dropkick a human brain. My best is twenty-one meters.
That's as good a promise as any, killer. Give the man what he needs.
Maliwan! They found us!
Hahaha! I have never seen Rhys squirm like that. You're really something, Vault Hunter.
Standing right here. The hologram can still hear you. And holo-Rhys has feelings.
Report! How's it looking?
Lots of movement, bandits and Maliwan patrols working together. We moved the civs into the tunnels just in case. And we've tried contacting Rhys, but Maliwan is jamming our comms.
Bollocks. Stay sharp, Skyman.||—C'mon, Vault Hunter. This way.
Re-establishing connection... come on...
You must defeat him. / I'll prevent counter-attack / during your battle.
Run!
Please don't shoot! I always buy Maliwan!
Right, so: I rigged up our drop pod with a Fast-Travel unit. Once you're planet-side, it'll hook up with the local network and you can come right back up.
We appreciate your patronage! Now hands above your heads!
Customer's always right, bitch!
We're close. Get ready. These guys aren't bandits—Maliwan's a well-equipped corporate army. We're gonna hit 'em hard, and make it hurt.

There's an Atlas base nearby with a direct line back to Rhys in HQ. Maliwan captured it a few months ago. I haven't had the manpower to take it back, but now that you're here, maybe we can finally send those bastards packing.
We're close. Get ready for a fight.
I'll get that blast door open!
You keep them off me, got it?
Trying to hotwire this door!
Got it! Door's open!

Now, it won't be what you call comfortable, or trustworthy, or safe by any measure. I'm just listing things, ain't no “but” at the end of that. 'Cept these two hams you been checking out. I saw ya! Anyway, get in and I'll launch ya.
All right, whatever works!
All right! Let's get that channel open to Atlas HQ.
Phew. All right. Connection to Atlas Headquarters is still intact. When you're ready, Vault Hunter.
In here!
Hi! You've reached Rhys Strongfork, CEO and wartime general of Atlas Corporation. Just a quick question...||WHO THE HELL IS THIS AND HOW DID YOU GET ON MY SECURE LINE?!
That weapons depot's a juicy target, but they've got an impenetrable security force-field surrounding it. If you somehow crack it open, you're gonna find some quality firepower in there.
Vault Hunt—||Crimson—||Holy crap, YES! How many troops did you bring? Twenty thousand? Fifty thousand?
Got me, got my mech. We'll be fine.
Depends. Do you count my biceps separately?
Fewer. My pack may be small... but our body count is high.
You don't need all that. I'm a one-man armada!
What? Come on! I can't take back this city with a single-digit army!
Greetings, Vault Hunter. Our mission is dangerous. First stop: this depot.
That looked like a rough ride. You still with us, killer?
Analog hacking.
The force-field's down? Brilliant! That weapons depot should be easy pickings now.

Perfect. Everybody's just piling on. Well, new friend, you showed up at the right time. My top agent is gearing up to strike at Maliwan's strategic Gigamind. If they are after the Vault, that's where the intel will be. Go meet up with my agent. Rhys out!
Are those Atlas dropships?
Are those Atlas dropships?
Incoming dropships. Is that Atlas?
No chance those dropships belong to Atlas, is there?
Negative.
That's the sword upgrade. / I need it for our mission. / I'll trade you for it.
Since you're heading downtown, I'm hooking you up with a Cyclone. It's fast and light, perfect for getting about the city streets. Take it for a spin.
That little sprig of mint gave you a new vehicle, huh? I'll make sure it's loaded into your Catch-A-Ride profile so you can digistruct a new one from any terminal.
Rhys' agent is bit of a loner, but he's got quite the knack for putting people's insides on their outsides. I'm sure you two'll hit it off just grand.
Hello, Vault Hunter. / Let's ruin Maliwan's day. / Our mission begins.
I think... I threw up my entire skeleton.
Ugh, that landing. I've been in gentler fistfights. Ngh.
I have no mouth and I must vomit.
Worst thing... that ever happened to me.||—LET'S DO IT AGAIN!
A ninja of few words. I like him.
What a curious person.||—That WAS a person, right?
Something familiar about that one.
I know that fella! We went to the same assassin bars.
That's Zer0. He used to be a Crimson Raider, like you. Wondered where he'd ended up. He's always been a little... cryptic, but he's as deadly as they come.
Thank you. Look at this. / Monomolecular edge. / Translation? Cool sword.
This fight is a test. / Show your true skill in battle. / I will be watching.
Their assault has failed. / A predictable outcome, / with our combined skills.
I'm good to go here. Place is compromised anyway. Let me know when you're ready.
Bandit technicals! Watch out!
Bandit outrunners, incoming!
Where the hell did these bandits get hover-wheels?! That's Maliwan tech!
Let's take one out, see if we can find where they're getting this stuff.
As long as you're alive. Looks like Ellie got you within the city limits. Go find whoever made that distress call.
With this new upgrade, / I can cut Maliwan shields. / Stand back and watch this.
Walls cannot hold us. / Now to take down Gigamind. / That is our mission.
What's a Gigamind and how do I kill it?
Is this “Gigamind” something I could punch?
I have never hunted a Gigamind. But I look forward to seeing it die.
Gigamind! Of course. I know it well. Mind explaining for anyone who doesn't, though? Uh, n-not me, of course.
Maliwan AI. / All their secrets in one place. / A juicy target.
So we gank Gigamind, we get access to their entire strategic database?
So we break Gigamind into tiny bits and then sift through them for info?
So we will crack open Maliwan's head and root around for secrets?
Sure. I've killed plenty of corporate AIs in my day. Great source of blackmail.
Precisely the plan. / Meet at Halcyon Spaceport. / Now the hunt is on.
Gigamind is here. / Expect intense resistance. / This is the fun part.
Nice! I see an ECHO in the wreckage. Grab it!
That bandit dropped an ECHO! Grab it!
Grab that ECHO!
This takeover won't be hostile for long. Atlas and Maliwan, we're hashing things out the corporate way. Rhys doesn't get it yet, but when this is over we'll all be one titanic happy family.
That guy is a douche. / And he's way obsessed with Rhys. / It's kind of creepy.
Okay. One more time, and I'm gonna say it slowly: don't kill the Maliwan guys.
KILL THE MALIWAN GUYS! FOR YOU! FOR MY QUEEN! FOR MY—
So. Not an AI. / Secrets locked in squishy brain. / Hack him. With your guns.
That will at least hold / recently processed data. / And thoughts during death.
Holdin' a brain. Cool.
It's... squishy?
I will keep it separate from the others.
Eh. I've touched worse.
Return to the base / and send that data to Rhys. / I have more to kill.
Oh, and Vault Hunter... / you are worthy of that name. / Good hunting with you.
It's a psycho!
No-no-no-no-no—okay, um...||This energy? I love it, but we made a DEAL with Maliwan, and now we're NOT going to kill them. So... what are we going to do when we see a Maliwan guy?
Hey! Vault Hunter! Did you get the data from Gigamind? Give it!
KILL THE MALIWAN GUYS! FOR TYREEN! FOR THE TWIN GODS!
Ooh, uh, yeah, that. Uh huh, it's just... I'm super busy with this whole invasion thing. Any other time, it is Vault o'clock, baby! But I've, I've got my company to look out for.
Yeah, okay, gotta start this one over.

Wait-wait-wait-w-wait, okay! Okay! Fine. I rebuilt Atlas from almost nothing, and I will do anything to keep Maliwan from taking that away. I swear on this company's future that I will help you find and open the Vault.
Grghaww!
C'mon, follow me.
Let me know when you're ready to take back that Atlas base.
You doing okay, love? Your family make it out?
Oh, bollocks! Maliwan's in the tunnels! Take 'em out!
Yeah. Most of them.
We'll make Maliwan pay. I promise.
You ready to move out? The base isn't far, but—
The force-field's down? Brilliant! Now that weapons depot should be easy pickings for our airborne units.
Wait, here's something.
Getting Atlas on our side would be a good start to finding the Vault here. If we can back them up, maybe they'll help us. Or at least not kill us while we search.
